column4: hey all, I had a security concept that I wanted to share about... I'm not sure it if makes sense or not.

I am very interested in the oAuth 2.0 JWT bearer token flow, as it allows us to not have to send passwords over the wire, however from my understanding on the initial send, a blank password request is sent which is answered by an nonce of sorts, so it should be transferred on the first request, right?
Well... I was wondering... what if we were to be able to encrypt the password in the browser using javascript, so it could be something like hmac(nonce + username + password + ip address).
what are the security risks in processing the data in-browser before it is sent out over the wire?

Hello, I have a question re: CSP, specifally in regards to report-uri. My question is: If the user agent is responsible for sending the report to the report-uri, how can you verify that its a legitimate report. What is to stop someone from generating a bunch of false positives by sending fake post requests to the report-uri ?
